The paper deals with modeling and analyzing cyber threats to air traffic control systems, which falls under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CR) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). The paper also uses a queuing network model to analyze the impact of these attacks, which falls under the category of systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses graph-level vulnerability metrics to identify vulnerable sectors, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS).
